cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.AI, cs.CYBER, cs.CR 

The paper focuses on the development of new influence maximization algorithms for interventions in social networks, which involves the intersection of social network theory and AI. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the deployment of these algorithms in real-world scenarios, which involves cybersecurity and privacy concerns, making cs.CYBER and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper utilizes techniques from sequential planning problems, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper addresses the challenges faced in deploying these algorithms in low-resource communities, which falls under the category of cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks).
